Sentencas: In this study, a 2-D numerical model is investigated to predict and evaluate the performance of an anode-supported SOFC button cell.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: The flow field is calculated using 2D Navier-Stokes equations.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: Heat and mass transfer equations are solved to calculate species and temperature distribution in the cell body and in fuel and air channels.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: The electrical and electrochemical processes are simulated coupled with the heat and mass transfer model.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: A discretized network circuit is adopted to the cell geometry for considering the ohmic losses and joule heating of the current that passes through the cell body.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: The model predicts the cell output voltage, the local EMF and the state variables pressure, temperature and species concentrations.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: The local electrical parameters are calculated based on the local pressure, temperature and concentration of the species.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: The numerical results are compared with the experimental data and good agreement is observed.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: The simulation is carried out for different input fuel flow rates and humidification.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: The results show how the input fuel mass flow rate and humidification level affects the button cell SOFC performance.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model

Sentencas: In addition, influences of the anode thickness on cell performance through the ohmic over potential are investigated.
Titulo: Performance analysis of a SOFC button cell using a CFD model
